## 5. Network Diagnostics & Low-Level Tooling

Network triage relies on raw ICMP, TCP, and DNS interrogation utilities to map infrastructure state and pinpoint connectivity faults.

### 1. `ping` (ICMP Echo Utility)
* **Underlying Engine:** Uses ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) Type 8 (Echo Request) and Type 0 (Echo Reply) frames at Layer 3 to test node reachability.
* **Core Metrics:** Calculates the round-trip time (RTT) latency and counts dropped packets to assess connection stability.
* **Command Implementation:**
  ```bash
  ping -c 5 -i 0.5 8.8.8.8
